## CONCLUSIONS

**1. Test Structure in resume_driver.test.cpp** (verilator/tests/hybrid/resume_driver.test.cpp)

**a) Building a RecordingBus** (lines 43-71):
```cpp
struct RecordingBus final : hybrid::DmiBus
{
  std::vector<DmiOp> ops;
  uint32_t dmstatus_value = 0;
  uint32_t abstractcs_value = 0;
  std::deque<uint32_t> abstractcs_queue;

  void write(uint8_t reg, uint32_t value) override
  { ops.push_back({DmiOp::Kind::Write, reg, value}); }

  auto read(uint8_t reg) -> uint32_t override
  {
    ops.push_back({DmiOp::Kind::Read, reg, 0});
    if (reg == kDmstatus) return dmstatus_value;
    if (reg == kAbstractcs) {
      if (!abstractcs_queue.empty()) {
        auto v = abstractcs_queue.front();
        abstractcs_queue.pop_front();
        return v;
      }
      return abstractcs_value;
    }
    return 0;
  }
};
```
The `RecordingBus` captures all DMI ops into a `std::vector<DmiOp>` with fields: `kind` (Write/Read), `reg` (DMI address), `value` (for writes). It is injected into `ResumeDriver` and supports per-register mock return values.

