**2. Test Structure in state_drain.test.cpp** (verilator/tests/hybrid/state_drain.test.cpp)

**Setting up RecordingBus with pre-programmed regfile** (lines 42-61):
```cpp
TEST_CASE("state_drain reads x1..x31 via Abstract Commands, skipping x0")
{
  RecordingBus bus;
  bus.dmstatus_value = kDmstatusHaltedAndAcked;
  for (uint16_t i = 0; i < 32; ++i)
    bus.regfile[hybrid::regno_gpr(i)] = 0xa00000000ULL + i;

  hybrid::StateDrain drain(bus);
  const auto state = drain.drain();

  for (int i = 1; i < 32; ++i)
    CHECK(state.gpr[i] == 0xa00000000ULL + i);
}
```
The `RecordingBus` (shared from recording_bus.hpp, line 40) stores a `std::unordered_map<uint16_t, uint64_t> regfile` that the test populates. On abstract-command reads, the bus latches `pending_data0/pending_data1` into DATA0/DATA1 registers so the driver reads the correct values.

**Asserting V-related reads with HYBRID_FLAG_V** (lines 239-274):
```cpp
TEST_CASE("drain_with_passthrough with HYBRID_FLAG_V: V CSRs read from DM, not input")
{
  RecordingBus bus;
  bus.dmstatus_value = kDmstatusHaltedAndAcked;

  bus.regfile[hybrid::regno_csr(RD::kCsrVstart)] = 7;
  bus.regfile[hybrid::regno_csr(RD::kCsrVxsat)]  = 1;
  bus.regfile[hybrid::regno_csr(RD::kCsrVxrm)]   = 2;
  bus.regfile[hybrid::regno_csr(RD::kCsrVcsr)]   = 5;

  hybrid_state_v1 input{};
  input.magic   = HYBRID_STATE_MAGIC;
  input.version = HYBRID_STATE_VERSION;
  input.flags   = HYBRID_FLAG_RV64 | HYBRID_FLAG_V;
  input.priv    = 3;
  input.vstart = 99;  // stale QEMU1 value

  hybrid::StateDrain drain(bus);
  const auto state = drain.drain_with_passthrough(input);

  CHECK(state.vstart == 7u);  // overwritten by DM read
}
```
Tests set `input.flags |= HYBRID_FLAG_V` and populate `bus.regfile[regno_csr(...)]` with post-vsim values. The `drain_with_passthrough()` method re-reads V CSRs from the DM (via abstract commands) and overwrites stale QEMU1 values.

