**3. Program-Buffer Tests in program_buffer.test.cpp** (verilator/tests/hybrid/program_buffer.test.cpp)

**exec_progbuf and cmderr assertion** (lines 99-119, 150-170):
```cpp
TEST_CASE("exec_progbuf: single instruction - writes insn, ebreak, exec command")
{
  RecBus bus;
  const std::array<uint32_t, 1> insns{0xDEADBEEFu};
  const bool ok = exec_progbuf(bus, insns);

  REQUIRE(ok == true);
  REQUIRE(bus.writes.size() == 3u);
  CHECK(bus.writes[0].reg == kProgbuf0);
  CHECK(bus.writes[0].val == 0xDEADBEEFu);
  CHECK(bus.writes[1].reg == kProgbuf0 + 1);
  CHECK(bus.writes[1].val == kEbreak);
  CHECK(bus.writes[2].reg == 0x17u);
  CHECK(bus.writes[2].val == kExecProgbufCmd);
}

TEST_CASE("exec_progbuf: clears sticky cmderr before issuing exec command")
{
  RecBus bus;
  constexpr uint32_t kCmderrMask = 0x7u << 8;
  bus.read_seq[0x16u] = {kCmderrMask, 0u, 0u};

  const std::array<uint32_t, 1> insns{0x1u};
  const bool ok = exec_progbuf(bus, insns);
  REQUIRE(ok == true);

  REQUIRE(bus.writes.size() == 4u);
  CHECK(bus.writes[2].reg == 0x16u);
  CHECK(bus.writes[2].val == kCmderrMask);
  CHECK(bus.writes[3].reg == 0x17u);
  CHECK(bus.writes[3].val == kExecProgbufCmd);
}
```
The pattern: (1) call `exec_progbuf(bus, insns_span)`, (2) inspect `bus.writes` order: progbuf0..N, ebreak, optional abstractcs W1C, then kExecProgbufCmd, (3) verify `bool ok` for post-exec cmderr state. Pre-cmderr is queued in `bus.read_seq[0x16u]` so it's returned on successive reads.

